item.title: Differences Between The Earths Lithosphere And Asthenosphere
item.description: The Earth’s lithosphere and asthenosphere are two separate layers of Earth’s interior. The lithosphere is the outermost and rigid layer of the Earth, while the asthenosphere is a layer of partially molten rock located beneath the lithosphere. Both layers play a vital role in the structure, dynamics, and evolution of Earth’s lithosphere. They provide the framework for the movement of tectonic plates and earthquakes, and the asthenosphere is responsible for the movement of magma.
